Rhinoceros: The Market Theatre Laboratory kicks off its 30-year anniversary celebrations with a production of Rhinoceros, written by Eugène Ionesco and directed by Mahlatsi Mokgonyana and Billy Langa. The play, performed by the Kwasha Theatre Company, takes a metaphorical look at the rise of totalitarianism on the eve of World War II.
